d, word or act)","kjv_def":"[idiom] exceeding, teach wisdom, be (make self, shew self) wise, deal (never so) wisely, make wiser.","pos":"verb","usage":"exceeding(1x)"},"H2450":{"id":"H2450","lemma":"חָכָם","translit":"châkâm","pron":"khaw-kawm'","derivation":"from H2449 (חָכַם);","strongs_def":"wise, (i.e. intelligent, skilful or artful)","kjv_def":"cunning (man), subtil, (un-), wise((hearted), man).","pos":"adjective","usage":"wise(109x), cunning(6x), subtil(1x), unwise(2x), wiser(2x)"},"H2451":{"id":"H2451","lemma":"חׇכְמָה","translit":"chokmâh","pron":"khok-maw'","derivation":"from H2449 (חָכַם);","strongs_def":"wisdom (in a good sense)","kjv_def":"skilful, wisdom, wisely, wit.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"wisdom(145x), wisely(2x), wits(1x)"},"H2452":{"id":"H2452","lemma":"חׇכְמָה","translit":"chokmâh","pron":"khok-maw'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H2451 (חׇכְמָה);","strongs_def":"wisdom","kjv_def":"wisdom.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"wisdom(8x)"},"H2453":{"id":"H2453","lemma":"חַכְמוֹנִי","translit":"Chakmôwnîy","pron":"khak-mo-nee'","derivation":"from H2449 (חָכַם); skilful;","strongs_def":"Chakmoni, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Hachmoni, Hachmonite."},"H2454":{"id":"H2454","lemma":"חׇכְמוֹת","translit":"chokmôwth","pron":"khok-moth'","derivation":"or חַכְמוֹת; collateral forms of H2451 (חׇכְמָה);","strongs_def":"wisdom","kjv_def":"wisdom, every wise (woman).","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"wisdom(4x)"},"H2455":{"id":"H2455","lemma":"חֹל","translit":"chôl","pron":"khole","derivation":"from H2490 (חָלַל);","strongs_def":"properly, exposed; hence, profane","kjv_def":"common, profane (place), unholy.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"profane(2x), common(2x), unholy(1x)"},"H2456":{"id":"H2456","lemma":"חָלָא","translit":"châlâʼ","pron":"khaw-law'","derivation":"a primitive root (compare H2470 (חָלָה));","strongs_def":"to be sick","kjv_def":"be diseased."},"H2457":{"id":"H2457","lemma":"חֶלְאָה","translit":"chelʼâh","pron":"khel-aw'","derivation":"from H2456 (חָלָא);","strongs_def":"properly, disease; hence, rust","kjv_def":"scum.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"scum(5x)"},"H2458":{"id":"H2458","lemma":"חֶלְאָה","translit":"Chelʼâh","pron":"khel-aw'","derivation":"the same as H2457 (חֶלְאָה);","strongs_def":"Chelah, an Israelitess","kjv_def":"Helah."},"H2459":{"id":"H2459","lemma":"חֶלֶב","translit":"cheleb","pron":"kheh'-leb","derivation":"or חֵלֶב; from an unused root meaning to be fat;","strongs_def":"fat, whether literally or figuratively; hence, the richest or choice part","kjv_def":"[idiom] best, fat(-ness), [idiom] finest, grease, marrow.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"fat(79x), fatness(4x), best(5x), finest(2x), grease(1x), marrow(1x)"},"H2460":{"id":"H2460","lemma":"חֵלֶב","translit":"Chêleb","pron":"khay'-leb","derivation":"the same as H2459 (חֶלֶב); fatness;","strongs_def":"Cheleb, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Heleb."},"H2461":{"id":"H2461","lemma":"חָלָב","translit":"châlâb","pron":"khaw-lawb'","derivation":"from the same as H2459 (חֶלֶב);","strongs_def":"milk (as the richness of kine)","kjv_def":"[phrase] cheese, milk, sucking.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"milk(42x), cheeses(1x), sucking(1x)"},"H2462":{"id":"H2462","lemma":"חֶלְבָּה","translit":"Chelbâh","pron":"khel-baw'","derivation":"feminine of H2459 (חֶלֶב); fertility;","strongs_def":"Chelbah, a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Helbah.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Helbah(1x)"},"H2463":{"id":"H2463","lemma":"חֶלְבּוֹן","translit":"Chelbôwn","pron":"khel-bone'","derivation":"from H2459 (חֶלֶב); fruitful;","strongs_def":"Chelbon, a place in Syria","kjv_def":"Helbah.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Helbon(1x)"},"H2464":{"id":"H2464","lemma":"חֶלְבְּנָה","translit":"chelbᵉnâh","pron":"khel-ben-aw'","derivation":"from H2459 (חֶלֶב);","strongs_def":"galbanam, an odorous gum (as if fatty)","kjv_def":"galbanum.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"galbanum(1x)"},"H2465":{"id":"H2465","lemma":"חֶלֶד","translit":"cheled","pron":"kheh'-led","derivation":"from an unused root apparently meaning to glide swiftly;","strongs_def":"life (as a fleeting portion of time); hence, the world (as transient)","kjv_def":"age, short time, world.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"age(2x), world(2x), time(1x)"},"H2466":{"id":"H2466","lemma":"חֵלֶד","translit":"chêled","pron":"khay'-led","derivation":"the same as H2465 (חֶלֶד);","strongs_def":"Cheled, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Heled."},"H2467":{"id":"H2467","lemma":"חֹלֶד","translit":"chôled","pron":"kho'-led","derivation":"from the same as H2465 (חֶלֶד);","strongs_def":"a weasel (from its gliding motion)","kjv_def":"weasel.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"weasel(1x)"},"H2468":{"id":"H2468","lemma":"חֻלְדָּה","translit":"Chuldâh","pron":"khool-daw'","derivation":"feminine of H2467 (חֹלֶד);","strongs_def":"Chuldah, an Israelitess","kjv_def":"Huldah."},"H2469":{"id":"H2469","lemma":"חֶלְדַּי","translit":"Chelday","pron":"khel-dah'-ee","derivation":"from H2466 (חֵלֶד); worldliness;","strongs_def":"Cheldai, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Heldai.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Heldai(2x)"},"H2470":{"id":"H2470","lemma":"חָלָה","translit":"châlâh","pron":"khaw-law'","derivation":"a primitive root (compare H2342 (חוּל), H2470 (חָלָה), H2490 (חָלַל));","strongs_def":"properly, to be rubbed or worn; hence (figuratively) to be weak, sick, afflicted; or (causatively) to grieve, make sick; also to stroke (in flattering), entreat","kjv_def":"beseech, (be) diseased, (put to) grief, be grieved, (be) grievous, infirmity, intreat, lay to, put to pain, [idiom] pray, make prayer, be (fall, make) sick, sore, be sorry, make suit ([idiom] supplication), woman in travail, be (become) weak, be wounded.","pos":"verb","usage":"beseech(6x), grievous(4x), wounded(3x), pray(3x), intreat(3x), grief(2x), grieved(2x), sore(2x), pain(1x), infirmity(1x), intreated(1x), laid(1x), prayer(1x), sorry(1x), supplication(1x), travail(1x)"},"H2471":{"id":"H2471","lemma":"חַלָּה","translit":"challâh","pron":"khal-law'","derivation":"from H2490 (חָלַל);","strongs_def":"a cake (as usually punctured)","kjv_def":"cake.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"cake(14x)"},"H2472":{"id":"H2472","lemma":"חֲלוֹם","translit":"chălôwm","pron":"khal-ome'","derivation":"or (shortened) חֲלֹם; from H2492 (חָלַם);","strongs_def":"a dream","kjv_def":"dream(-er).","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"dream(64x)"},"H2473":{"id":"H2473","lemma":"חֹלוֹן","translit":"Chôlôwn","pron":"kho-lone'","derivation":"or (shortened) חֹלֹן; probably from H2344 (חוֹל); sandy;","strongs_def":"Cholon, the name of two places in Palestine","kjv_def":"Holon.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Holon(3x)"},"H2474":{"id":"H2474","lemma":"חַלּוֹן","translit":"challôwn","pron":"khal-lone'","strongs_def":"a window (as perforated)","kjv_def":"window.","pos":"masculine/feminine noun","usage":"window(31x)"},"H2475":{"id":"H2475","lemma":"חֲלוֹף","translit":"chălôwph","pron":"khal-ofe'","derivation":"from H2498 (חָלַף);","strongs_def":"properly, surviving; by implication (collectively) orphans","kjv_def":"[idiom] destruction."},"H2476":{"id":"H2476","lemma":"חֲלוּשָׁה","translit":"chălûwshâh","pron":"khal-oo-shaw'","derivation":"feminine passive participle of H2522 (חָלַשׁ);","strongs_def":"defeat","kjv_def":"being overcome.","pos":"feminine noun"},"H2477":{"id":"H2477","lemma":"חֲלַח","translit":"Chălach","pron":"khal-akh'","derivation":"probably of foreign origin;","strongs_def":"Chalach, a region of Assyria","kjv_def":"Halah."},"H2478":{"id":"H2478","lemma":"חַלְחוּל","translit":"Chalchûwl","pron":"khal-khool'","derivation":"by reduplication from H2342 (חוּל); contorted;","strongs_def":"Chalchul, a place in Palestine","kjv_def":"Halhul.","pos":"proper locative noun","usage":"Halhul(1x)"},"H2479":{"id":"H2479","lemma":"חַלְחָלָה","translit":"chalchâlâh","pron":"khal-khaw-law'","derivation":"feminine from the same as H2478 (חַלְחוּל);","strongs_def":"writhing (in childbirth); by implication, terror","kjv_def":"(great