-tsaw'","derivation":"from H2503 (חֶלֶץ);","strongs_def":"spoil","kjv_def":"armour.","pos":"feminine noun","usage":"spoil(1x), armour(1x)"},"H2489":{"id":"H2489","lemma":"חֵלְכָא","translit":"chêlᵉkâʼ","pron":"khay-lek-aw'","derivation":"or חֵלְכָה; apparently from an unused root probably meaning to be dark or (figuratively) unhappy;","strongs_def":"a wretch, i.e. unfortunate","kjv_def":"poor.","pos":"adjective","usage":"poor(2x), variant(2x)"},"H2490":{"id":"H2490","lemma":"חָלַל","translit":"châlal","pron":"khaw-lal'","derivation":"a primitive root (compare H2470 (חָלָה)); also  denominative (from H2485 (חָלִיל))","strongs_def":"properly, to bore, i.e. (by implication) to wound, to dissolve; figuratively, to profane (a person, place or thing), to break (one's word), to begin (as if by an 'opening wedge'); to play (the flute)","kjv_def":"begin ([idiom] men began), defile, [idiom] break, defile, [idiom] eat (as common things), [idiom] first, [idiom] gather the grape thereof, [idiom] take inheritance, pipe, player on instruments, pollute, (cast as) profane (self), prostitute, slay (slain), sorrow, stain, wound.","pos":"verb","usage":"begin(52x), profane(36x), pollute(23x), defile(9x), break(4x), wounded(3x), eat(2x), slay(2x), first(1x), inheritance(1x), piped(1x), players(1x), prostitute(1x), sorrow(1x), stain(1x)"},"H2491":{"id":"H2491","lemma":"חָלָל","translit":"châlâl","pron":"khaw-lawl'","derivation":"from H2490 (חָלַל);","strongs_def":"pierced (especially to death); figuratively, polluted","kjv_def":"kill, profane, slain (man), [idiom] slew, (deadly) wounded.","pos":"adjective, masculine noun","usage":"slay(78x), wounded(10x), profane(3x), kill(2x)"},"H2492":{"id":"H2492","lemma":"חָלַם","translit":"châlam","pron":"khaw-lam'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to bind firmly, i.e. (by implication) to be (causatively to make) plump; also (through the figurative sense of dumbness) to dream","kjv_def":"(cause to) dream(-er), be in good liking, recover.","pos":"verb"},"H2493":{"id":"H2493","lemma":"חֵלֶם","translit":"chêlem","pron":"khay'-lem","derivation":"(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to H2492 (חָלַם);","strongs_def":"a dream","kjv_def":"dream.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"dream(22x)"},"H2494":{"id":"H2494","lemma":"חֵלֶם","translit":"Chêlem","pron":"khay'lem","derivation":"from H2492 (חָלַם); a dream;","strongs_def":"Chelem, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Helem. Compare H2469 (חֶלְדַּי).","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Helem(1x)"},"H2495":{"id":"H2495","lemma":"חַלָּמוּת","translit":"challâmûwth","pron":"khal-law-mooth'","derivation":"from H2492 (חָלַם) (in the sense of insipidity);","strongs_def":"probably purslain","kjv_def":"egg."},"H2496":{"id":"H2496","lemma":"חַלָּמִישׁ","translit":"challâmîysh","pron":"klal-law-meesh'","derivation":"probably from H2492 (חָלַם) (in the sense of hardness);","strongs_def":"flint","kjv_def":"flint(-y), rock.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"flint(3x), flinty(1x), rock(1x)"},"H2497":{"id":"H2497","lemma":"חֵלֹן","translit":"Chêlôn","pron":"khay-lone'","derivation":"from H2428 (חַיִל); strong;","strongs_def":"Chelon, an Israelite","kjv_def":"Helon.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Helon(5x)"},"H2498":{"id":"H2498","lemma":"חָלַף","translit":"châlaph","pron":"khaw-laf'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to slide by, i.e. (by implication) to hasten away, pass on, spring up, pierce or change","kjv_def":"abolish, alter, change, cut off, go on forward, grow up, be over, pass (away, on, through), renew, sprout, strike through.","pos":"verb","usage":"change(10x), pass(3x), renew(3x), abolish(1x), alter(1x), over(1x)"},"H2499":{"id":"H2499","lemma":"חֲלַף","translit":"chălaph","pron":"khal-af'","derivation":"(Aramaic) corresponding to H2498 (חָלַף);","strongs_def":"to pass on (of time)","kjv_def":"pass.","pos":"verb","usage":"pass(4x)"}}